			<div class="content" id="post-content-4853708">
									

<p>Hi there. This is my first SCP draft so here is the link to my greenlights: <a href="https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/forum/t-13902889/singularity-seeking-greenlight-1-2">Idea Thread</a></p>
<p>I've made some major changes per the suggestions made in that thread and would like your feedback. Some things I'm looking for critique on include: clinical tone, line by line, general formatting, and emotional impact, although critique of any kind is appreciated. I also think that dialogue is one of my weaker points as a writer, so I'm definitely looking for opinions on that.</p>
<p>Here's the link to my sandbox: <a href="http://scp-sandbox-3.wikidot.com/dr-hajovsky">http://scp-sandbox-3.wikidot.com/dr-hajovsky</a></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Major&nbsp;Updates</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Major&nbsp;Updates</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>01-03-21:</p>
<p>-Cut all of the testing logs in favor of a singular addendum that I feel gets the intended effects of the anomaly across in a much more clear fashion. This should hopefully help the article feel more concise and focused.</p>
<p>-Made some notable changes to the description and the recovery log.</p>
<p>-Made some changes to dialogue to make absolutely sure the theme of the story was conveyed, as well as address other minor concerns.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

