			<div class="content" id="post-content-4853869">
									

<p>Thanks for the feedback and suggestions!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>My first main concern is that you didn't cite your image.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The photo is actually something I took and uploaded myself. Would I still need to cite the image or is it fine since it's mine?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The focus of your is on Licht's character arc, but your logs are pretty detached from that. You can also cut down on the description of SCP-####-A through -I by having there only be one button that lets Licht move outside of the flow of time, and then just letting him walk around outside of time instead of using multiple other buttons to do so.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I did want to have some test logs to give the story a bit more time to sink in and develop, as well as flesh out the abilities of the SCP in the reader's minds. However, I do agree that these can be distracting. I attempted to keep them out of the way in collapsibles, but if they are really an issue I can remove them.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I'd put a footnote briefly defining &quot;gravitational lensing&quot;, since I imagine most readers won't know what that is.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I didn't really think of that. Nice catch. I'll be sure to add it in the footnotes.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>with genetic matches to theirs were discovered at [DATA EXPUNGED]<br />
<br />
I don't understand why this is redacted. I'd recommend reading this guide</p>
</blockquote>
<p>In my mind, this was redacted to conceal information about the way in which the foundation disposes of staff that die by anomalous means. If it ends up a big issue, I'm open to removing it and writing something in its place.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>If you want to center a collapsible while having the text inside the collapsible be left-aligned, you can do it with this code:<br />
<br />
As a general note, a good way to learn formatting is to look at the page source of other articles (click &quot;+Options&quot; at the bottom of a page and then click &quot;Page Source&quot;)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Thanks, I had no idea how this was done properly.</p>
<p>I'll make sure to correct the smaller grammatical and logistical errors you pointed out, as well as try to find better descriptors while keeping with the clinical tone.</p>
</div>
</div>
